        <mxCell id="8EPcR9BEbHYVh53qIw0D-67" parent="1" style="whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;align=left;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;We will be using tags on the table level to to drive some of the logic on the Databricks side.&amp;nbsp; Each table will have a primary key that will be used for insert/update/delete operations, an optional &#39;pruned&#39; indicator, TTL for the pruned tables, and the column used for TTL.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;If a table is marked as &#39;pruned&#39; at the table level or schema level the delete messages will be ignored.&amp;nbsp; It will just upsert data to the target tables (with have the schema name/table name as the sources).&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;otherwise, the code will apply deletes then upsert the new data.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
